rick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Enrique, Alejandro, Alicia, Angel.  Italian Ricardo, Marco, Vito, Armando, Arturo, Celestino, Eduardo, Elvira, Ettore, Vincenzo.","Catalan (<b>Guàrdia</b>), Spanish, and Italian: from Catalan <i>guàrdia</i>, Spanish and Italian <i>guardia</i> ‘guard, watch’, a topographic name for someone who lived by a watch place, by a watchtower, or a habitational name from any of numerous places called (La) Guardia, named with the same word; or a metonymic occupational name for someone who kept watch or for a member of the town guard. Compare Italian   Laguardia   2."],"variants":[{"name":"Laguardia","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Carlos, Alberto, Anabella, Andres, Armando, Efrain, Elvira, Emilia, Evelio, Fernando, Genaro.  Italian Antonio, Cono, Enrico, Rocco, Sal, Santo.","Spanish: habitational name from Laguardia in Araba/Álava province, Basque Country. Compare   De la Guardia  .","Italian (also <b>La Guardia</b>): variant of   Guardia   ‘guard, watch’, with the addition of the definite article <i>la</i>."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Guarda Saxon was born on 21 March 1236, in Saxony, Germany. She married Stefanos Torun in 1275, in Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died on 11 June 1276, at the age of 40, and was buried in Thorn, Renfrewshire, Scotland."},"et":{"21 March 1235/1236–11 June 1276":"21. märts 1236–11. juuni 1276","1224–1293":"1224–1293","1276–1336":"1276–1336","1236–1276":"1236–1276","1336":"1336","1236":"1236","1224":"1224","1276":"1276","1275":"1275","11 June 1276":"11. juuni 1276","21 March 1235/1236":"21. märts 1236","1293":"1293","1 April 1276":"1. aprill 1276","Neidersachten, Saxony, Europe":"Sachsen, Saksamaa","Toruń, Kuyavia-Pomerania, Poland":"Toruński, kujawsko-pomorskie, Poola","Torun graveyard":"Thorn, Renfrewshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"21 March 1235/1236–11 June 1276":"21. maaliskuuta 1236–11. kesäkuuta 1276",